Algorithms

Algorithms While thinking about the algorithms, one should consider the tradeoffs between time complexity (average and worst case), space complexity, and lines of code needed. Below is a compiled list of basic and advanced algorithms:
  • Sieve of Erastothenes
  • Recursion
  • Quicksort
  • Merge Sort
  • Dynamic Programming
  • Depth First Search
  • Binary Search
  • Breadth First Search
  • Backtracking
